      "writtenOn": "2026-05-06T15:49:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "A few comments here:\n* During a system power on, PSM may chose not to power some chassis on. The chassis could be missing, in hardware isolation, have a bad power status, etc.\n* I think we want chassis 0 to only show that the system is powered on when all the chassis **selected for power on** are powered on. So it should change to On last after the chassis, and the power state should not take into account chassis not selected for power on.\n* During a system power off, PSM may chose not to power some chassis off. For example, if the Available property is being used to indicate whether communication is possible, it may not be possible to power some chassis off.\n* I think we want chassis 0 to only show the system is powered off when all the chassis **selected for power off** are powered off. So it should change to Off last.",
      "revId": "b6dd3731158759f5c73a23828467024115fec41a",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
